      <div>
        <h2 id="how-consent-works" class="t-h3">How consent works here</h2>
        <p>When you first visit, a banner offers three equal choices: accept optional cookies, reject optional cookies, or manage preferences category by category. Nothing optional is ever switched on before you choose. You can reopen your choices at any time using "Cookie Settings" in the footer of every page, or the button above.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 id="categories" class="t-h3">Categories explained</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Essential</strong> — always on. Required for the site to work at all, including remembering your cookie choice itself.</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics</strong> — off by default. Controls whether Plausible, a cookieless analytics service, loads to show us anonymised visit counts and popular pages.</li>
          <li><strong>External media</strong> — off by default. Controls whether embedded YouTube videos load automatically, or stay behind a placeholder you can load individually.</li>
          <li><strong>Preferences</strong> — off by default. Controls whether your light/dark theme choice is remembered between visits.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We found no marketing, advertising, or campaign-tracking tool anywhere in this site's code, so a "Marketing" toggle is not shown in Cookie Settings. If that ever changes, this policy and the preference panel will be updated together, before any such tool is added.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 id="table" class="t-h3">The cookies and storage we use</h2>
        <p>This table is generated from a full review of this website's code — nothing on it is guessed. "Provider-controlled or not confirmed" means the exact duration is set by the third party and was not confirmed as part of that review.</p>
        <div class="legal-table-wrap">
        <table class="legal-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Cookie or storage key</th><th>Provider</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Category</th><th>Duration</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>vw-consent</code> (localStorage)</td>
              <td>Verdandi Weaver (this website)</td>
              <td>Stores your cookie choices — version, timestamp, which categories you accepted or rejected, and how (accept all / reject all / custom) — so we don't ask again every visit.</td>
